data.title: What Happened on October 10, 1965
data.meta_description: What happened on October 10, 1965. Browse historical events, famous birthdays and notable deaths from Oct 10, 1965 or search by date, day or keyword.
data.text:
Historical Events

"Drat! - The Cat!" opens at Martin Beck Theater NYC for 8 performances

"Vinland Map" is introduced by Yale University as being the first known map of America, drawn about 1440

TV Show Appearance

The Supremes appear on the "The Ed Sullivan Show"

Famous Birthdays

Chris Penn, American actor (The Wild Life), born in Los Angeles, California (d. 2006)

Rebecca Pidgeon, British-American actress, singer and songwriter, born in Cambridge, Massachusetts

Steve Scalise, American politician (Representative-R-Louisiana 2008-), born in New Orleans, Louisiana

Toshi, Japanese singer (X Japan), born in Tateyama, Chiba, Japan

About October 10, 1965

Day of the Week: Sunday
